main event: On March 25, 1953, a woman in Panama City, Florida observed a circular, silvery unidentified flying object over the area.
interesting points: The object was hovering and flying straight and level towards Panama City.
The observer was the only one to report the sighting, and she made the observation from inside her house looking out the window.
Since the object was quite far away, the observer could not determine the distance or altitude.
There were a minimum of 30 jet aircraft in the general vicinity of Panama City at the time of the sighting, and the object could have been a reflection of one of those jets.
No photographs or fragments of the object were obtained.
sighted object: a circular, silvery unidentified flying object
